All guide articles follow the same component pattern: `PullQuote`, `SectionLabel`, and where applicable a `ScienceBox` callout. All fragrance name references link to the catalog where the slug exists in the database; missing slugs render as plain pills.

### Guide index filtering
`src/app/guide/page.tsx` is now a client component with four filter tabs: All, Psychology, Family Deep Dives, Buying Guides. Each article has a `category` field. Article count updates live as filters are applied.

## Current state of the full app

### Routes
- `/` — hero, featured fragrances, scent family tiles
- `/fragrances` — catalog with filter sidebar (family, price, occasion, season)
- `/fragrances/[slug]` — full detail: notes pyramid, dual-register toggle, dupes, similar, reviews, collection button
- `/houses` — listing grouped by tier
- `/houses/[slug]` — house detail with fragrance grid
- `/notes` — notes library with pagination and position drill-down
- `/notes/[slug]` — note detail
- `/search` — search results
- `/dupes` — alternatives browser (new this session)
- `/guide` — filterable index (13 articles)
- `/guide/[slug]` — 13 article pages
- `/sign-in`, `/sign-up` — Supabase auth forms
- `/auth/callback` — Supabase OAuth callback
- `/profile` — wardrobe with stats, filter tabs, edit modal

### Infrastructure
- Next.js 16.2.4, Prisma, PostgreSQL via Supabase (project ref: hnsnmjwdpewgivphxkcn)
- Auth: Supabase Auth
- Deployed: Vercel, auto-deploy on push to `main`
- TypeScript: zero errors
- Database: 158 houses, 358 notes, 684 fragrances, 23 dupes, 1540 similar pairs

## What is not yet built

- **SEO metadata** — no `<title>` or `<meta description>` on any page. High-leverage for organic discovery. Recommended next.
- **Mobile nav** — current nav collapses poorly on small screens. Not a blocker but noticeable.
- **Pagination on /fragrances** — catalog currently loads all 684 fragrances at once. Should paginate.
- **Layering guidance page** — was in the original design, data model supports it, no page built.
- **More family deep dives** — Gourmand and Chypre families have no articles yet.

## Conventions to preserve

- Guide articles: always check fragrance slugs against the database before writing. Missing slugs render as plain pills (the `FragLinks` / `FragPill` pattern handles this). Never invent a slug.
- Guide articles: `PullQuote` and `SectionLabel` components are defined inline in each page file — not shared. This is intentional; each page is self-contained.
- Nav order: Catalog · Houses · Notes · Dupes · Guide · Search · Wardrobe/Sign in.
- Commits: one commit per discrete feature, imperative subject line, Co-Authored-By trailer.
